titleInfo.title: USA v. Christensen et al
titleInfo.subTitle: MEMORANDUM DECISION AND ORDER as to Trina Christensen re 119 Competency Hearing, (Notice sent to USM). Defendant Trina Christensen is incompetent to stand trial at the present time and shall be committed to the custody of the Attorney General for a period not to exceed 120 days for the purpose of undergoing restorative treatment. The current pre-trial and trial dates are vacated and will be re-set if necessary after conducting a second competency hearing once the defendant has undergone her restorative treatment. Signed by Judge B. Lynn Winmill.(caused to be mailed to non Registered Participants at the addresses listed on the Notice of Electronic Filing (NEF) by jm) (cc: USP by jm).
